Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.02,0:02:15.02,Default2,Chapter,0,0,0,Part 1,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.46,0:02:15.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,430)\i1}Fingers... eyes... lips.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.92,0:02:20.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}When we were little, it started as our secret language.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.24,0:02:23.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1\t(3217,0,1,\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&HFFFFFF&\4c&HFFFFFF&)}When we were separated into different Houses, it was no longer just a game.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.66,0:02:27.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If our families found out, we would face much worse than a scolding.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.75,0:02:30.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We were completely closed off.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.50,0:02:34.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This was the only way we could speak freely with one another.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.50,0:02:37.53,Current Episode Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(947.6,640.6)}Episode 4:\NThe Connected Women
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.08,0:02:37.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,Miri and Miyo really creep me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.51,0:02:40.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,Always talking about something, but never saying a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.89,0:02:46.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,Yet, that skill of theirs is particularly useful when it comes to gambling.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.88,0:02:50.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,Torn apart by a succession struggle, those two sisters devised a perfect method
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.73,0:02:52.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,of secret communication.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.97,0:02:56.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,Undetectable to ordinary eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.15,0:03:00.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,I'm quite jealous that they stayed so close after being separated.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.15,0:03:02.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,Rin-san, we're plenty close.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.91,0:03:10.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,Between those sisters and Jabami Yumeko... \NI wonder who Lady Luck will smile on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.18,0:03:12.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,Rei, what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.78,0:03:16.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,I find gambling rather baffling, I'm afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.00,0:03:19.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,You never change, do you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.93,0:03:26.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He deliberately showed everyone his hand.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.43,0:03:29.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A weak hand, with no zeros at that.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.43,0:03:31.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How foolish can one be?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.05,0:03:34.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Three, two, zero, zero.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.90,0:03:38.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Indeed. Three, three, two, zero.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.19,0:03:40.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We both have zeros.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.82,0:03:42.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Our numbers are on the high side,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.36,0:03:44.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But we can win.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.95,0:03:47.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's start with Miri-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.33,0:03:52.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If I can bring the total to nine on my turn, Suzui loses.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.30,0:03:55.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I can open up by playing a three.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.42,0:03:57.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Then you can adjust as needed, Miyo.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.76,0:04:00.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's a good idea...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.22,0:04:03.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...but I have a better one.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.72,0:04:05.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,Three.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.60,0:04:08.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,Our first play is a three. Now for Suzui-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.60,0:04:10.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,R... r-right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.38,0:04:16.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,Suzui.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.09,0:04:18.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,Play a one.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.15,0:04:20.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.36,0:04:24.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,Just do as I say. So we can win.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.14,0:04:29.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,All right. In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.37,0:04:31.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,Is that really what you want, Suzui-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.62,0:04:32.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.62,0:04:35.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,Saotome-san is trying to sacrifice you {look, allie}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.42,0:04:37.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,to make sure she wins.  {look, allie}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.10,0:04:40.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,That's why she made you reveal your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.43,0:04:43.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,But, you know, if you lose this game...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.18,0:04:45.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,You will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.70,0:04:53.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,Ah! How about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.02,0:04:56.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,If you ignore what Saotome-san tells you,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.18,0:04:58.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,I'll provide you some antidote as a gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.87,0:05:02.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,Enough for both you and Yumeko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.28,0:05:03.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.40,0:05:07.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,You're risking your life because you want to save her, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.64,0:05:10.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,With this antidote, you could save Yumeko-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.41,0:05:13.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,and you would no longer need to risk your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.95,0:05:18.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,Nor would you need to play along with the cajolery of that coward.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.52,0:05:21.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,You have no choice but to betray her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.30,0:05:24.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to fret about.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.76,0:05:28.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,Come, let's bring down Saotome-san together.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.25,0:05:36.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,No, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.65,0:05:38.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.31,0:05:39.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,No, thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.12,0:05:44.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,Oh, does it bother you to condemn Saotome-san to death?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.68,0:05:47.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,In that case, I can provide enough for her...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.78,0:05:48.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.62,0:05:51.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,Your way would be no fun at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.70,0:05:53.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,And that's not what Yumeko wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.50,0:05:56.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,It's not what I want!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.96,0:06:00.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,Second card is a one! The total is four!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.25,0:06:03.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,How disappointing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.09,0:06:05.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,You have him well trained, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.22,0:06:08.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,Allow me to enlighten you, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.09,0:06:12.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,The weak are exploited until the day they die.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.10,0:06:16.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,Oh! Third card is a two. The total is six!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.55,0:06:18.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,We're almost in the danger zone!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.68,0:06:20.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Why a two?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.87,0:06:24.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Due to our turn order, we are unable to make Saotome lose this round.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.36,0:06:28.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Let's first focus on killing Suzui.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.86,0:06:31.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}With the total at six,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.37,0:06:34.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}if Saotome plays a one or a three, then Suzui will lose.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.11,0:06:38.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The only way to avoid it is by playing a two.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.42,0:06:42.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But Saotome's best play is a three, since it raises the total the most for Miri's turn.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.30,0:06:45.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,Well, Saotome-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.05,0:06:46.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,It's your turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.36,0:06:49.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,What were you saying, just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.50,0:06:52.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,Who was being exploited?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.54,0:06:54.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,The weak, you see—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.14,0:06:57.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,Who are "the weak", here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.71,0:06:55.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,Tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.64,0:07:00.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,Why, you two, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.60,0:07:03.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,You've been forced to bet your precious 100 votes,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.15,0:07:05.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,and your life is in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.15,0:07:09.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,And we are only betting the antidote we already have.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.34,0:07:11.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,That's the difference between the strong and the weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.46,0:07:14.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,That may be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.50,0:07:17.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,But you've got one thing wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.04,0:07:22.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,We're in Hyakkao Academy. The weak ones here...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.29,0:07:25.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,Are you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.55,0:07:29.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,Fourth card is a two! The total is eight!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.05,0:07:31.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Drat. She's lucky.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.35,0:07:33.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We'd have won if I had a one.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.00,0:07:35.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I have no choice.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.02,0:07:38.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,Fifth card is a zero! The total is eight!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.18,0:07:41.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,Sixth card is a one! The total is nine!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.19,0:07:44.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,Seventh card is a zero! The total is nine!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.56,0:07:47.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,Next is Mary-chan! If you don't have a zero, you're dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.53,0:07:50.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Miri has no more zeros.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.95,0:07:53.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If I have to take another turn...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.07,0:07:56.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'll lose.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.85,0:07:58.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,Obviously I have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.70,0:08:02.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,Eighth card is a zero, and the total is nine!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.29,0:08:04.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,Next up is Miri-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.13,0:08:06.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,Got any zeros?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.88,0:08:07.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.09,0:08:11.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,W-we did it! We won!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.34,0:08:13.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,Round 2, complete!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.34,0:08:17.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,Youbami Miri loses, and must pay 33 votes to the winners!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.04,0:08:19.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,Since we can't split up one serum,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.89,0:08:21.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,if that's how you want to pay,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.18,0:08:23.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,how about you give 'em one each?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.01,0:08:27.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,This is the antidote?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.86,0:08:30.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,Great! This will do fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.62,0:08:33.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,But there's something else you need to do, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.36,0:08:36.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,The loser needs to prick their finger on these needles.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.42,0:08:39.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,Miyo, I don't have any serums left.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.18,0:08:42.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,Please bring me one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.37,0:08:45.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,How do you use this thing? I need to give it to Yumeko soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.50,0:08:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,Huh? What are you guys talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.56,0:08:51.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,You still have another round of Nim Zero to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.26,0:08:54.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,You can't spend your chips while the game is still going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.76,0:08:58.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,No using those serums until we're all finished!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.00,0:08:59.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,You can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.02,0:09:01.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,No arguing with the dealer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.77,0:09:08.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It will be a little while before the poison takes effect.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.65,0:09:11.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Finishing this game will be a piece of cake.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.66,0:09:15.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}More importantly, we need to teach Saotome a lesson.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.96,0:09:17.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}About the taste of death.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.53,0:09:18.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.71,0:09:27.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,Now, it's time for round 3!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.17,0:09:28.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,I'll deal the cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.14,0:09:32.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Right now, we have two serums.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.39,0:09:35.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If either Saotome or I lose this round...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.67,0:09:39.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We'll lose our serum and get poisoned.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.41,0:09:42.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We won't have enough antidote!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.65,0:09:44.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,Suzui?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.55,0:09:47.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.69,0:09:51.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This foolishness, again? He must have a death wish.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.93,0:09:53.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,Let's start the betting!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.19,0:09:55.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,Suzui-kun, how about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.95,0:09:57.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,I bet five votes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.98,0:10:01.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,I raise you 300 votes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.69,0:10:04.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}300 votes!?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.28,0:10:07.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is she trying to make up for her prior loss?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.04,0:10:07.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,I raise...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.22,0:10:10.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,10,000 votes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.25,0:10:11.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.34,0:10:16.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,Nyahahaha!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.38,0:10:17.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,10,000 votes?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.48,0:10:21.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,That's 240,000 hours, you know! You'll grow old at this school!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.35,0:10:22.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,Is there a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.85,0:10:25.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,Not at all, not at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.02,0:10:27.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,But if you lose...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.35,0:10:31.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,You'll have to retire from the presidential election.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.88,0:10:35.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Miyo.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.43,0:10:41.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Saotome's goal is clear. She wants us to fold.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.52,0:10:45.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Now that she has a serum, she has no reason to play.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.03,0:10:46.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What should we do?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.54,0:10:49.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She's obviously bluffing.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.29,0:10:53.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You're right. If her hand were strong, she'd have made a reasonable bet.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.54,0:10:59.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In any case, this girl called us weak. She needs to die.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.80,0:11:00.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,I call.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.05,0:11:04.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,Dumbass.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.43,0:11:05.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,Call.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.77,0:11:06.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,Call.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.25,0:11:09.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,Okay! The bet is 10,000 votes. Let's begin!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.69,0:11:13.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,Suzui, play a two.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.44,0:11:15.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.32,0:11:17.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How can she make that face?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.57,0:11:19.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,The total is two!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.07,0:11:22.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Saotome should be paralyzed with fear by our absolute force.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.87,0:11:25.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She's a total weakling!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.22,0:11:27.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,Second card is a three! The total is five!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.83,0:11:29.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How can this be?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.28,0:11:32.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Only the strong can smile like that.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.41,0:11:35.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,Third card is a two! The total is seven!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.07,0:11:40.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Even if Saotome had a great hand, Suzui definitely didn't.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.69,0:11:42.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She should be in deep water right now.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.68,0:11:44.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Miyo.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.43,0:11:47.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's bad that she played a two.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.43,0:11:50.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}With the total at seven, I can only play a one.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.43,0:11:55.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If I do, Suzui will play a one, and then it'll be your turn with the total at nine.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.44,0:11:58.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If only I had a two, we'd have a chance.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.70,0:12:03.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,Didn't I tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.38,0:12:07.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,You two are the weaklings here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.06,0:12:10.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We should have been able to win.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.46,0:12:15.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Miri and I have good hands. We both have zeros.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.96,0:12:18.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}With our bond, we should have been able to win!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.46,0:12:22.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And yet, we're the ones under threat right now.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.47,0:12:25.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's all her fault!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.72,0:12:29.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,Oh? Did you finally notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.08,0:12:32.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,Did you not realize something was up?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.85,0:12:35.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,Were you not at all suspicious
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.65,0:12:37.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,about the way the dealer dealt the cards?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.84,0:12:40.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.36,0:12:44.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,She used a Gilbreath shuffle. It's a famous trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.00,0:12:49.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,You take a deck of cards that alternate between the four suits, spades, hearts, clubs, and diamonds.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.87,0:12:54.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,You cut it at random, and pile up as many cards as you like in a stack.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.42,0:12:57.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,Then you riffle shuffle the two stacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.63,0:12:59.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,The deck order appears to be random,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.92,0:13:04.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,but in reality, every four cards will contain one of each suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.63,0:13:07.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,It's the same as this game, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.10,0:13:16.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,That means that the 16 cards we were randomly dealt contained precisely four cards of each number.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.90,0:13:20.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,Why do you think I made Suzui reveal his cards?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.69,0:13:23.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,Because I wanted to win for myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.29,0:13:24.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,Too bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.28,0:13:25.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,Wrong answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.28,0:13:31.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,By knowing Suzui's cards and adding them to my own, I determined what the other eight cards were.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.35,0:13:36.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,In other words, I knew exactly which cards you two had.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.79,0:13:40.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,You guys never had a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.04,0:13:41.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.34,0:13:46.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,Suzui, do you notice anything\N if you add my cards to yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.68,0:13:48.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,Huh? Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.82,0:13:51.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,Th... there's a trend?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.18,0:13:54.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,Right. We have all the twos.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.48,0:13:59.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,So the choices you two could make were limited, which made you easier to predict.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.44,0:14:03.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,Our victory was certain from the moment the cards were dealt.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.69,0:14:08.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,Although, Suzui... You believed in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.22,0:14:10.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.88,0:14:12.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,Y... you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.83,0:14:17.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,Anyway, you guys were from the Momobami Clan? That's really something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.83,0:14:21.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,Betting 10,000 votes on a gamble you can't even win...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.46,0:14:24.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,I sure don't have the guts for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.09,0:14:26.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,Ahahaha! Ahahaha!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.25,0:14:26.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.26,0:14:30.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,A special shuffle...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.18,0:14:33.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,Doesn't that mean the dealer planned the whole thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.35,0:14:36.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,It's unfair. What happened to neutrality?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.35,0:14:39.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,Huh? You still don't get it, do you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.85,0:14:42.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,You're saying I wasn't neutral?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.36,0:14:46.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,You better watch your mouth, child.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.36,0:14:49.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,I was dealing the same way the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.99,0:14:52.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,It's your fault for not noticing, Miyo-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.87,0:14:56.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,In any case, I used this dealing method to prevent uneven distributions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.79,0:14:59.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,It wasn't to put anyone at a disadvantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.87,0:15:05.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,W-well, that said, anyone who doesn't notice has a pretty lethal disadvantage!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.93,0:15:12.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,You put so much faith in poisons and brute force that you neglected your powers of observation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.89,0:15:15.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,You said that I planned the whole thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.39,0:15:19.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,but isn't it natural that the dealer gets to set the rules?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.14,0:15:22.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,It's my job to set the rules so that anyone can win!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.32,0:15:25.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,Even if some players use a weapon like poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.40,0:15:31.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,You can't use brute force to stop someone from wanting to gamble.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.60,0:15:36.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,Anyone can take anyone down.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.16,0:15:38.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,That's my absolute neutrality!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.53,0:15:41.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,That school rule is the cornerstone of my existence!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.67,0:15:44.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,If someone dies in this election...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.38,0:15:47.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,I'll just create a game that even dead people can win.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.34,0:15:52.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,Now, let's get back to the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.68,0:15:54.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,Miri-chan, it's your turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.44,0:16:04.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,Oh? You don't look so good.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.94,0:16:07.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,Poison getting to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.19,0:16:09.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,Hurry up and play a card.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.19,0:16:11.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,Let's get this over with.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.20,0:16:19.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,Fourth card is a one, and the total is eight! It's time for the climax!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.36,0:16:23.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I can't... There's nothing I can do.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.46,0:16:24.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But...!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.51,0:16:26.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,A one! The total is nine!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.46,0:16:29.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,Zero! The total is nine!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.47,0:16:33.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,Zero! The total is nine!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.47,0:16:36.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,Alright, Miri-chan! Your turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.27,0:16:39.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If I play this, Miyo will...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.47,0:16:42.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Onee-chan will lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.99,0:16:46.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,Miri,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.86,0:16:48.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,play a three.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.13,0:16:52.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.36,0:16:58.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,If one of us has to lose, better you than me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.58,0:17:01.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,After all, I'm more talented.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.94,0:17:05.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,It would be a bigger problem if I were eliminated from the election.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.63,0:17:08.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,Come on. Lose, Miri.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.79,0:17:13.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,Lose, and prick your finger on the needles. Let's get this over with.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.83,0:17:18.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,Do you not want my antidote?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.14,0:17:27.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,Hurry up, Miri.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.40,0:17:34.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,Three! The total is twelve! Youbami Miri loses!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.02,0:17:39.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,What's up, Miri-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.91,0:17:43.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,Oh, dear. She fainted. What should we do about the punishment?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.46,0:17:47.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,Does it matter? The game is over, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.54,0:17:52.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.05,0:17:56.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,I don't want to hear "But you were merciful then!" next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.48,0:18:01.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,Saotome Mary.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.93,0:18:04.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,Next time, I {\i1}will{\i0}  kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.04,0:18:07.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,Bring it on.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.07,0:18:15.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,She's looking a lot better.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.69,0:18:17.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,She should be all right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.50,0:18:21.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,If you two hadn't won, she would have been in serious danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.33,0:18:24.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,The antidote seems to be working properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.95,0:18:27.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,Honestly, I was worried about that. {allie, look!}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.96,0:18:30.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,I will now take my leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.33,0:18:32.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Batsubami-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.59,0:18:36.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,We didn't know how to apply the serum by ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.23,0:18:39.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,Oh, I am simply glad I could be of service.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.44,0:18:41.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.52,0:18:45.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,Saotome!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.85,0:18:48.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.73,0:18:51.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,You're the reason Yumeko is still alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.90,0:18:56.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,I-it's not like I could just let her die!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.40,0:18:59.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,Y-yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.03,0:19:01.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,You really were a godsend.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.88,0:19:04.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,Yumeko never ceases to amaze.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.54,0:19:08.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,You know what she said after she collapsed from the poison?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.99,0:19:12.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,She told me that if I called you there, I'd have a good time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.54,0:19:13.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.54,0:19:17.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,Even though her life was in danger, Yumeko just...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.64,0:19:23.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is Yumeko we're talking about. She must have noticed the Gilbreath shuffle.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.98,0:19:27.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But she didn't know that I'd notice,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.47,0:19:30.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}or that I could use that to win.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.34,0:19:35.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yumeko is willing to bet even her own life.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.42,0:19:38.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She's a genuine gambling addict.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.70,0:19:41.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But I'm not like that.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.10,0:19:46.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If anyone's worthy of being student council president at this insane academy...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.33,0:19:51.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,Hey, everybody!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.08,0:19:54.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,Thanks so much for coming to see me today!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.58,0:19:57.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,I've been waiting for this, Yumemi{**-chan}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.92,0:19:59.09,Default2,,0,0,0,,Did you all bring your votes? {\an8}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.09,0:20:01.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.06,0:20:04.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\c&H158BC8&\3c&H158BC8&\4c&H158BC8&\t(0,308,1,\c&HF1F1F1&\3c&H131374&\4c&H000000&)}Come again soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.48,0:20:12.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,Showdown.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.68,0:20:16.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,The table has two, two, ace, seven, six.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.16,0:20:23.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,Joumaru-sama has two pair, aces and twos.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.95,0:20:30.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,Momobami-sama has two pair with aces and twos as well, but her kicker card is a nine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.84,0:20:33.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,Because her kicker is higher, Momobami-sama wins.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.71,0:20:44.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,I couldn't come close. It was like I was under your thumb from start to finish.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.22,0:20:47.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,Oh, my! Good luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.92,0:20:51.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,This is so dull, Sayaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.82,0:20:54.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,Why do you partake of this nonsense?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.60,0:20:59.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,Is there no one who will sincerely try to take me out?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.99,0:21:05.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,Well, how about us?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.10,0:21:07.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.28,0:21:09.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,Finally, a bit of fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.47,0:21:16.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,Hey! Batsubami-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.13,0:21:19.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,Hi there. Thanks for the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.88,0:21:21.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,Suzui-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.30,0:21:23.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,Yumeko's gotten a lot better.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.68,0:21:25.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.88,0:21:27.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,Th... that's quite alright...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.17,0:21:29.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,U-um...!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.76,0:21:34.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,I'm, um... the one you rescued yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.52,0:21:36.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,Ah... you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.77,0:21:39.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,You were like a prince...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.11,0:21:41.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, I didn't mean!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.40,0:21:43.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.10,0:21:45.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,Please take this, if you like!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.95,0:21:50.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,Cats.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.16,0:21:54.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,I only thought of the Momobami Clan as frightening,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.01,0:21:58.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,but you're a kind person, Batsubami{**-san}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.05,0:22:05.59,Infirmary Sign2,,0,0,0,,{\pos(257.6,306.8)\frz9.682}Second Year
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.05,0:22:05.59,Infirmary Sign2,,0,0,0,,{\frz10.06\pos(259.2,511.6)}Flower Class
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.05,0:22:05.59,Infirmary Sign3,,0,0,0,,{\frz7.841\pos(507.2,266.8)}Jabami
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.05,0:22:05.59,Infirmary Sign,,0,0,0,,{\frz9.479\pos(859.2,202.8)}Yumeko
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.09,0:22:12.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The election is going to get even\N more heated from now on.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.55,0:22:16.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And I know you're going to jump right into the thick of it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.60,0:22:21.27,Default2,,0,0,0,,Yumeko, I don't know if you can hear me,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.27,0:22:23.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,but you're the only one I'm going to tell this to.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.97,0:22:27.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,I'll only say it once.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.12,0:22:35.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,Yumeko, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.97,0:22:39.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,will become student council president.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.00,0:22:42.00,ED,Chapter,0,0,0,ED,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.49,0:23:03.30,ED,,0,0,0,,If you desire it so much as to writhe, I will give it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.49,0:23:03.29,ED,,0,0,0,,{\an8}notautsu hodo ni motomeru no nara ataeyou
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.30,0:23:07.60,ED,,0,0,0,,You will need to avail yourself of even your despair.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.29,0:23:07.60,ED,,0,0,0,,{\an8}zetsubou sae kate ni shite shimau
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.60,0:23:10.91,ED,,0,0,0,,Now, come to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.60,0:23:10.91,ED,,0,0,0,,{\an8}saa oide
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.91,0:23:17.02,ED,,0,0,0,,If you offer your body and soul, I will answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.91,0:23:17.02,ED,,0,0,0,,{\an8}mi mo kokoro mademo sashidasu nara kotaeyou
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.02,0:23:22.62,ED,,0,0,0,,Tragedy will be overwhelmed by pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.02,0:23:22.62,ED,,0,0,0,,{\an8}higeki mo etsuraku ni nomareru
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.62,0:23:30.27,ED,,0,0,0,,Consumed by an excess of pure carnal desire,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.62,0:23:30.27,ED,,0,0,0,,{\an8}amari nimo sekirara na retsujou ni ukasarenagara
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.27,0:23:38.27,ED,,0,0,0,,Eventually you will live wishing only for a moment of titillation.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.27,0:23:38.27,ED,,0,0,0,,{\an8}yagate shibireru youna shunkan dake wo negai ikiru
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.28,0:23:46.37,ED,,0,0,0,,O soul that burns with desire, raise your glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.28,0:23:46.37,ED,,0,0,0,,{\an8}aa katsubou suru tamashii yo sakazuki wo kakage
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.37,0:23:53.14,ED,,0,0,0,,Sing an ode to such joy as will break you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.37,0:23:53.14,ED,,0,0,0,,{\an8}kowareru hodo kanki no uta wo utaou
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.14,0:24:00.00,ED,,0,0,0,,Simple acclaim will never satisfy your cravings.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.14,0:24:00.00,ED,,0,0,0,,{\an8}kassai dewa michitaru hazu mo nai uzuki
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.00,0:24:06.88,ED,,0,0,0,,It's maddening enough to bet on.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.00,0:24:06.88,ED,,0,0,0,,{\an8}kakeru hodo kuruoshii
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.51,0:22:58.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,{ED start}
